frameDefinitions: A Useful_location is accessible to some (possibly generic)
A building or location that can be sealed to prevent entrance, the Locale, ceases to be open for use.

A less-powerful person or group of people (the Activists) engages in an activity aimed to inconvenience or weaken a more powerful person or group (the Institution) to seek redress, in the form of a series of Demands, for the wrondgoings committed by the Instituion.  '
A Ratifier responds to a Proposal constructed by another party to make it binding over the Ratifier's jurisdiction or constituency.
An Entity ends up with some Final_quality--a new fact about the Entity.
An Agent manipulates a Fastener to open or close a Containing_object (e.g. coat, jar).
frameExamples: I left the door to the lobby <t>open</t> for you.
The workers were <t>striking</t> for better wages and better benefits.
The <t>ratification</t> of the Kyoto protocol has been a long, hard slog.
Mary <t>closed</t> her coat with a belt.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Theme</fen> whose motion is blocked or free.
The place or thing that the <fen>Theme</fen> is headed towards, despite a potential or actual <fen>Barrier</fen>.
An entity that (at least potentially) prevents the <fen>Theme</fen> from getting to the <fen>Useful_location</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Useful_location</fen> is or is not accessible.
The <fen>Locale</fen> is the entity that ceases to be available for use.
The <fen>Time</fen> of the closure.
The <fen>Place</fen> of the failing locale.
The person or group of people that act out against the <fen>Institution</fen> in an attempt to have their <fen>Demands</fen> fullfilled.
The <fen>Institution</fen> is the company, factory, political party / institution, or entity that yields authority over the <fen>Activists</fen>.

The <fen>Demands</fen> are the guarantee(s) given by the <fen>Institution</fen> to the <fen>Activists</fen> that act to correct or address the issues or state of affairs that were grievous to the <fen>Activists</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the location where the political action occurs.

The individual or body that confirms a Proposal negotiated or created by another party, causing it to become binding in a jurisdiction represented by the <fen>Ratifier</fen>.  In the case of direct democratic ratification, the jurisdiction and the <fen>Ratifier</fen> are the same.
The idea or course of action proposed by another individual or body which the <fen>Ratifier</fen> endorses and makes binding.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Ratifier</fen> makes the <fen>Proposal</fen> binding.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the <fen>Ratifier</fen> ratifies the <fen>Proposal</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change, newly ending up in the <fen>Final_category</fen> or taking on a new <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
A description of a characteristic of the <fen>Entity</fen> after the change.
The category that the <fen>Entity</fen> ends up in after the change.  Typically, this entails taking on a number of new characteristics.
>When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.

This role identifies the item that is closed by the agent with the fastener.
<fex name='Agent'>Lee</fex> <t>buttoned</t> <fex name='Containing_object'>his coat</fex>.
The Agent opens/closes the Containing-object.
This role identifies the fastener that the agent manipulates.
This role identifies the active zone of the container that may be expressed as the direct object of the target verb.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> closes the <fen>Container_portal</fen> or the <fen>Containing_object</fen>.
The location where the closing event takes place.
